People wearing masks walk on a street in Ankara, Turkey on July 8, 2020. Turkey's COVID-19 cases increased by 1,041 on Wednesday, while the total cases climbed to 208,938, Turkish Health Minister Fahrettin Koca said. (Photo by Mustafa Kaya/Xinhua)Turkey's COVID-19 cases increased by 1,041 on Wednesday, while the total cases climbed to 208,938, Turkish Health Minister Fahrettin Koca said.Meanwhile, 22 people died in the past 24 hours, taking the death toll to 5,282, the minister said at a press conference.Turkish health professionals conducted 49,302 tests in the past 24 hours, bringing the overall number of tests to 3,782,520, he added.

